				<p><p>Ian's answer is mathematically correct.  However, on most processors division takes longer than multiplication.  So if you're at all pressed for processor resources you would want to precalculate a gain and offset for each channel, and apply it:</p>

<p>$k_{zz} = \frac{1}{S_{zz}}$</p>

<p>$b_{zz} = -\frac{B_z^{0g}}{S_{zz}}$</p>

<p>$a_{z1}^{corrected} = k_{zz} a_{z1} + b_{zz}$</p>
</p><br>
